2022 season comes to and end… 2023 LOADING…

If I could get to here… you can get to anywhere you want too. 

This was nothing but a dream at one point. A vision I wanted to make a reality. So I worked really damn hard for a really long time and made it happen. I made mistakes and learned lessons. I got knocked down and got back up, over and over. But I got here. Now my vision is bigger, and I’m working harder… I’m just a girl from Winnipeg who followed through on the promises she made to herself. Nothing was given to me, every single opportunity I had to intentionally create on my own. 

This year, follow through on the promises you make to yourself. Be disciplined with you habits, and get back up every time you fall… and you WILL get there. Stay determined to your course. Work hard and be good to people. This is YOUR life to make it what you want it to be. Don’t let the opinions of others dictate the decisions you make for yourself. Stay true and authentic to who you are and who you want to become.

Go get it!! 

#2023 #dothework

From 35th to 6th. 

We got up to 3rd at one point & thought we were gonna take the lead before the caution came out.

@venturinimotorsports brought us a fast car! We Lost power steering with 4 to go but still held on to it. All in all had a blast. 

Big thanks to @IconDirect @glenmcleodsons for making this all possible! 

& thank you to all of you for all of your support!! 🏁

It’s RACEDAY!! Starting P3 today at Talladega.

So disappointed, thought yesterday was going to be our day.

Had a really strong run going at Kansas in our @venturinimotorsports @icontechltd #15 
Until I pushed it too hard and stepped over the edge. 

When you’re fighting for sponsorship race after race, every race feels like it could be your last and there is immense pressure to perform and get your desired results. Most of that pressure is self induced when you want this as bad as I do.

I was really giving it my all out there, and sometimes as drivers we push our limits a little too much. Proud of the speed we showed, and running the top was really fun but disappointed in my mistake. I have a lot to reflect on and you all know I’ll be fighting to add more races to our schedule this season, so stay tuned for that. 

Thank you for all the support ❤️

GRAN TURISMO: BASED ON A TRUE STORY is the ultimate wish fulfillment of Jann Mardenborough who went from gamer to racer! I am so excited about this film because I really resonate with the story. Being a female in a male dominated industry, and being someone that doesn’t come from money, trying to break into a very expensive sport has had its challenges. But when the odds are stacked against you, you become that much more driven to succeed! It’s cool to see a movie made that’s so realistic and close to my own story! I love that the Gran Turismo movie is so realistic and accurately shares what it really takes to be a professional race car driver. This sport is a lot tougher than most people think and this movie does a good job of showing the different aspects of what it takes to be a driver! I can’t wait to grab some popcorn and watch GRAN TURISMO: BASED ON A TRUE STORY exclusively in movie theaters and IMAX on August 25th! Tickets on sale now. 
#GranTurismoMovie #ad @sonypicturescanada

Big smile and dirt on my face. Wouldn’t change it for anything.

As disappointing as it was not to race full time this season, I was still grateful to receive opportunities to race in different racing series and was able to continue developing my skills. 

At the end of last year I really assessed where I needed to be better and used this season to improve on those things. 

And that we did. I have never had more belief in my ability as a driver nor been in this great of a place mentally. I am more ready than ever for that next big opportunity and you better believe I’m working towards that! 

Thank you to those who support me whether I’m full time or part time, racing nationally or locally. It means the world to me! 

Special thanks to @leefaulkracing @brimstonegames519 @glenmcleodsons for helping with my development this season and @icontechltd for allowing me to run at some of NASCARs most legendary tracks!

My Intention is to be back behind the wheel full time in 2024 at a national level and I’m currently working on making that happen! 

“We got a long way to go and a short time to get there, we gonna do what they say can’t be done” :)

I am Amber Balcaen and I am fueled by purpose. 

Being able to share my voice and story with @ShellStationsUS #PerformanceUnbound Series reminds me of the raw passion, dedication, and the unrelenting pursuit of excellence that drives me on the track. 

I will continue to push boundaries and redefine what’s possible in the world of racing. Shell’s commitment to innovation resonates with my own drive for perfection, and I’m thankful for every supporter, every team member, and everyone who’s been part of this incredible journey! #ShellVPower #PerformanceUnbound

Very grateful to be one of the first few recipients to receive the @shiftupnow foundation Grant. 

This grant allowed me to test with @leefaulkracing this week to continue developing my skills this off season so that I am sharp and prepared for my return to a national NASCAR series in 2024. 

Every time I work with @leefaulkracing I get better and better. I feel really good about the progress I’ve made with them this season. These tests are vital to my development and I can’t thank @shiftupnow enough for making this possible!

So take the step. The only way to overcome fear is through action.
